Trueshot Longbow Quest<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
 This Quest is assigned by Maesyn Trueshot of the Ranger’s Guild in Kelethin. The minimum level for this quest is Level 8 with a Fletching Skill of 101+. I found that with a Fletching skill of 103 I had about a 1 and 10 chance of success to make this bow. Therefore I recommend gathering enough materials for 10 attempts. Although, I have heard many stories of low-level characters with a fletching skill as low as 10 getting lucky and making one of these.<br>
<br>
Maesyn Trueshot will give you a Material Pack (4 slots) and you will have to get the following items and combine them in the pack: Micro Servo, Spool of Dwarven Wire, Treant Wood, and a piece of Spiderling Silk. <br>
<br>
In Kaladim: Get the Spool of Dwarven Wire from Trantor Everhot in North Kaladim. To actually get the wire, you have to bring him 2 Tumpy Tonics from Tumpy Irontoe in South Kaladim. Tumpy will tell you that in order to make that brew, he needs a Kiola Nut and a Flask of Water. Kiola Nuts can be bought at the Inn on the Isle of Erollisi in Ocean of Tears. This island is the first docking spot when traveling from Freeport to Butcherblock Mountains. When the boat docks at the island, you actually have time to run to the Inn, buy the nuts, and make it back on the boat before it departs to Butcherblock.<br>
<br>
In Freeport: Go to the Hogcaller’s Inn in West Freeport. Upstairs you will find Jyle Windshot. He will tell you that he lost his lantern in a game of chance in Highhold Pass and that he needs a replacement. You need to give him a small lantern which can be bought off many merchants. I found these lanterns at the Freeport Inn in East Freeport. Just give Jyle the lantern and he will give you a piece of Treant Wood (I think it just says wood).<br>
<br>
Steamfont Mountains: Hunt down and kill Clockworks (metal spiders) to obtain the Micro Servo that can be found on some of their bodies. There are 3 types of Clockworks: Rogue, Runaway, and large Rogue Clockworks. They all can drop the Micro Servo. The best way to get the Micro Servo is to shout to all the players (low level gnomes) that if they find a Micro Servo to send you a tell with the location. These items are no drop and they are useless to most gnomes. You can pay for the service but I have found that these low level gnomes would prefer Buffs and Heals. <br>
<br>
You can get the Spiderling Silk from any zone that has any kind of Spiderlings.<br>
<br>
Once you have one of each item, combine them in the Material Pack and give this back to Maesyn Trueshot. He will reward you with the Treant Bow Staff.<br>
<br>
NOW, to make the Trueshot Longbow, you have to do combine the following items in a Fletching Kit:<br>
1 Treant Bow Staff<br>
1 Micro Servo <br>
1 Spool of Dwarven Wire<br>
1 Planing Tool (can purchased at Tureshot Bows #24 on map in Kelethin)<br>
If you succeed in making the bow, you will have the Trueshot Longbow. If you fail you will only be left with the planing tool.<br>
<br>
Keep in mind if you want to find a master fletcher to combine the items in a fletching box for you: Dwarven Wire is no drop but the ingredients are not. The person doing the fletching will have to give the ingredients to Tumpy Irontoe. And, a Micro Servo is a no drop item. The person doing the fletching will have to loot this item.<br>
<br>
Ingredients for 10 attempts at making the Trueshot Longbow:<br>
20 Micro Servo<br>
40 Kiola Nuts – cost about 2 pp each<br>
40 Flasks of Water<br>
10 Small Lanterns<br>
10 Spiderling Silks<br>
1 Planing tool.<br>
